# =============================================================================
# Root .dockerignore — applies to test Dockerfiles (Dockerfile.*.test)
# whose build context is the repo root. Without this, the build context
# balloons to ~360 MB (node_modules + .NET build output + .git).
# Per-directory .dockerignore files also exist under backend/ and frontend/.
# =============================================================================

# --- VCS ---
.git
.gitignore
.gitattributes

# --- Docs & planning (not needed at build time) ---
*.md
HANDOFF_P1.md
README*.md
TECH_NOTES*.md
COMP9900_project_list.md
GitHub_Issues_by_Sprint.md
Database_ER_Diagram.md
P14_Modern_Ecommerce_Web_App.md

# --- .NET build output & caches ---
**/bin/
**/obj/
**/.vs/
*.user
*.suo

# --- Node (only present locally; never send to Docker) ---
**/node_modules/
**/.next/
**/.out/
**/npm-debug.log*
**/yarn-error.log*

# --- Python (lanely/bili artefacts if co-located; harmless otherwise) ---
**/__pycache__/
**/venv/
**/.venv/

# --- Environment & secrets ---
.env
.env.*
!.env.example

# --- IDE & OS ---
.vscode/
.idea/
.claude/
.cursor/
.DS_Store
Thumbs.db
*.swp
*.swo

# --- Docker meta (avoid recursive context) ---
Dockerfile*
.dockerignore
docker-compose*.yml

# --- Local data volumes ---
postgres_data/
redis_data/
